# Figma MCP Workflow

When pulling a design from Figma:

1. Use `get_design_context` to get the component structure
2. Use `get_variable_defs` to extract design tokens/variables
3. Use `get_screenshot` for visual reference
4. Map Figma variables to CSS custom properties in `src/tokens.css`
5. Convert generated Tailwind code to plain CSS using the project's token system
6. Download image/SVG assets from the Figma MCP localhost server into `src/assets/`

# Asset Handling

- If Figma MCP returns a localhost source for an image or SVG, download it to `src/assets/`
- Do not use placeholder images when real assets are available
- Do not add icon packages -- use assets from the Figma payload
